891
01:19:26,705 --> 01:19:32,990
not only of public access, but for televising, what do you call it, bandwidth and broadband.

892
01:19:33,470 --> 01:19:39,715
So these are all technical things that are beyond my imagination for understanding, but all I know is having an understanding.

893
01:19:39,955 --> 01:19:50,643
But when they turn around and put a picture of our present mayor on a story with other mayors saying that he was a shill for Comcast, and he was a shill, and they went down to explain

894
01:19:51,170 --> 01:20:00,840
that the reason is because on an annual basis, got $10,000 a year for a celebration committee, got $2,500 each and every year for his golf tournament.

895
01:20:01,200 --> 01:20:06,426
And when you start thinking about that and you hear people talk about it, they're saying, wait a minute, we're not paying.

896
01:20:06,626 --> 01:20:09,829
I'm not paying my cable bill so he can have a golf tournament every year.

897
01:20:10,069 --> 01:20:13,393
I'm not paying my cable bill so he can have a celebration committee.

898
01:20:13,887 --> 01:20:17,149
And that's a cost that's built right in to everyone's cable fee.

899
01:20:17,189 --> 01:20:18,689
Comcast isn't giving this for nothing.

900
01:20:19,169 --> 01:20:26,953
They know what the cost is to give out those perks to those 52 mayors who signed on and were termed shills for Comcast.

901
01:20:27,393 --> 01:20:35,997
That's a hell of a way to go out of office, being known that you were shill, leaving the city all upside down with these crazy meters in the square, and God knows what else is going to happen.

902
01:20:36,677 --> 01:20:37,858
The fact of the matter is,

903
01:20:38,164 --> 01:20:44,749
We have a terrible contract here with Comcast, and nothing should be signed until a new mayor comes on board.

904
01:20:45,210 --> 01:20:48,912
So if we have to stay on as nothing more than a tenant, so be it.

905
01:20:49,413 --> 01:20:59,681
I'm going to ask that this council make a request that the mayor does not sign any new 10-year contract with Comcast and until a new administration comes on board.

906
01:21:00,221 --> 01:21:01,042
Isn't it interesting?

907
01:21:01,404 --> 01:21:05,087
They took the same thing when they were trying to hire a new public works director.

908
01:21:05,367 --> 01:21:07,710
They went through the whole process, and then they decided to stop.

909
01:21:08,050 --> 01:21:09,151
Let the new mayor come in.

910
01:21:09,371 --> 01:21:10,852
Let the new mayor hire that person.

911
01:21:11,313 --> 01:21:13,635
Well, we have enough 10-year contracts to deal with.

912
01:21:13,915 --> 01:21:20,401
We have a rubbish contract that I believe was in its seventh year, and it was re-upped for another 10 years when they renewed it.

913
01:21:21,241 --> 01:21:25,025
We have a stupid kiosk program that's a 10-year contract.

914
01:21:25,405 --> 01:21:27,767
And we have a contract right now that's not in operation,

915
01:21:28,063 --> 01:21:31,866
which is the tail end of a Comcast contract, which is all over, it's expired.

916
01:21:32,607 --> 01:21:36,349
So if we have to sit around and being tenants at will, so be it, so to speak.

917
01:21:36,590 --> 01:21:49,800
But I don't think the mayor should do anything, anything, to indulge this community into another 10-year contract without having a say, and especially not having a public hearing in advance before any contract negotiation took place.

918
01:21:50,320 --> 01:21:56,165
So I move that resolution, Mr. President, that the Memphis City Council go on record and respectfully request the mayor

919
01:21:56,712 --> 01:22:00,553
not to engage and not to sign any contract with Comcast.

920
01:22:01,693 --> 01:22:05,395
Until there's a new mayor.

921
01:22:05,615 --> 01:22:06,715
Until a new mayor is sworn in.

922
01:22:07,735 --> 01:22:09,416
On that motion, Councilor Knight.

923
01:22:10,536 --> 01:22:23,340
Mr. President, I believe we did pass a resolution on 324.15, as I look at my resolution tracking sheet, paper number 15306, asking the mayor do not sign a 10-year Comcast contract.

924
01:22:25,053 --> 01:22:27,994
I'm not sure how this paper would differ from the paper that was previously passed.

925
01:22:28,054 --> 01:22:29,555
Is it so that he doesn't sign any contract?

926
01:22:29,575 --> 01:22:31,476
He doesn't negotiate into any contract at all?

927
01:22:32,476 --> 01:22:35,698
You know, I question the body's ability to take away powers of the executive.

928
01:22:35,718 --> 01:22:36,798
There's a separation of powers.

929
01:22:36,818 --> 01:22:39,039
The executive has certain powers in the community.

930
01:22:39,319 --> 01:22:40,840
We can make recommendations all we want.

931
01:22:40,880 --> 01:22:41,560
I think we've done that.

932
01:22:41,580 --> 01:22:46,002
I think we've expressed to him that we want a member on the negotiating committee, a member of this committee on the negotiating committee.

933
01:22:46,803 --> 01:22:49,484
I think that was part of the resolution, paper 15306.

934
01:22:49,824 --> 01:22:54,546
So I guess my question is, how does this paper differ from the paper that was passed previously?

935
01:22:55,035 --> 01:22:58,858
The difference between this paper and that one, we now are dealing with a contract that's expired.

936
01:22:58,918 --> 01:23:05,662
Number one, we're dealing with the national attainment hearing that's taking place this Thursday that should have come before the fact, and it's now coming after the fact.

937
01:23:06,082 --> 01:23:17,269
What the mayor intends to accomplish by doing this, and it was this council that voted 7 to 11 to have that hearing take place at 6, 630 at night to allow taxpayers who couldn't have an opportunity to come at 2 o'clock in the afternoon.

938
01:23:17,589 --> 01:23:20,411
We're now dealing with a contract that's already been—that's expired.

939
01:23:20,852 --> 01:23:23,213
You are talking about a contract that was still in operation.

940
01:23:23,613 --> 01:23:24,714
Now, with no contract,

941
01:23:24,997 --> 01:23:33,582
and having no direction from the mayor, this is a respectful request that he does not sign any contract with Comcast until on and after a new mayor has been sworn in.

942
01:23:35,423 --> 01:23:43,327
Mr. President, I don't see how this paper is really much different than the last one that was filed then, and I question the council's ability to actually take a power away from the executive branch.

943
01:23:43,768 --> 01:23:47,090
You know, I certainly think that a 10-year contract is bad.

944
01:23:47,130 --> 01:23:47,830
I certainly think that

945
01:23:48,217 --> 01:24:05,422
in the future as we start negotiating these municipal contracts, that a member of the council should be included in the participation in the discussions, Mr. President, for the simple fact that we can avoid situations like this, where we have a conflicted council, a council that's in blatant disagreement with the length of the term of the contract, and an administration that doesn't feel as though that's quite the case.

946
01:24:05,542 --> 01:24:07,783
They think a tenure contract might be in the best interest of the community.

947
01:24:08,623 --> 01:24:16,226
With that being said, Mr. President, you know, do we have the authority to tell the man that he doesn't have the right to perform the essential functions of his job before he leaves?

948
01:24:16,606 --> 01:24:17,166
I don't think we do.

949
01:24:17,590 --> 01:24:19,470
Well, point of further information, Mr. President.

950
01:24:19,650 --> 01:24:21,791
Point of further information, Council Penta.

951
01:24:21,871 --> 01:24:27,212
Council Knight just included a resolve that was passed earlier this year, which I'm assuming he voted for.

952
01:24:27,312 --> 01:24:29,572
And now he's trying to say, what right do we have to interfere?

953
01:24:29,992 --> 01:24:37,153
Well, the mayor has already acknowledged it by noting that he's not going to hire a new Department of Public Works director at $120,000 plus a year.

954
01:24:37,413 --> 01:24:38,434
And he's letting that go.

955
01:24:38,654 --> 01:24:43,215
He's already set the channels in one particular direction on an appointment.

956
01:24:43,735 --> 01:24:46,035
Did the council receive a paper to that effect?

957
01:24:46,294 --> 01:24:46,574
Pardon me?

