01:26:01,609 --> 01:26:02,469
You're all set, Councillor Knight.

983
01:26:02,789 --> 01:26:02,969
Yes.

984
01:26:03,230 --> 01:26:03,770
Councillor Marks.

985
01:26:04,390 --> 01:26:05,671
Thank you, Mr. President.

986
01:26:05,811 --> 01:26:12,796
And I, for one, and I don't think my other colleagues are saying that we're going to try to circumvent the mayor's powers.

987
01:26:12,856 --> 01:26:17,178
We know under the city charter, he has the authority to sign contracts.

988
01:26:17,579 --> 01:26:24,603
I think what we're saying is common sense should prevail that the mayor is going to be leaving in several months.

989
01:26:25,263 --> 01:26:32,325
And I don't think anyone should have the ability to strap their predecessor in for a 10-year contract.

990
01:26:33,025 --> 01:26:36,266
And, you know, that's where I stand on the issue.

991
01:26:36,887 --> 01:26:43,809
Regarding the ascertainment hearing, Councilor Penta has been bringing this up week after week, along with other citizens.

992
01:26:43,889 --> 01:26:49,170
But we did vote to move this to 6 p.m., which the mayor denied.

993
01:26:49,771 --> 01:26:54,212
So, residents in the community, people that have a full-time job and can't make a

994
01:26:54,625 --> 01:26:57,827
two in the afternoon meeting here at City Hall would be able to attend.

995
01:26:59,689 --> 01:27:01,290
There's two points that I wanted to bring up.

996
01:27:01,330 --> 01:27:09,997
The first one is the connectivity that we've been talking about before this council for, it's gotta be at least 10 years now, on Riverside Avenue Square.

997
01:27:10,017 --> 01:27:14,540
There's a number of businesses on there that can't get internet access.

998
01:27:15,481 --> 01:27:16,142
Why is that?

999
01:27:16,482 --> 01:27:22,967
In this day and age, why do you have a section of your downtown business district that doesn't have access to the internet?

1000
01:27:23,347 --> 01:27:24,508
It just boggles my mind.

1001
01:27:24,973 --> 01:27:36,181
That would be the first thing that, if I was signing the contract, that I would make sure whatever hurdles they have to jump over, that they're going to jump over to make sure everyone has access in that particular square.

1002
01:27:36,741 --> 01:27:47,969
It was also brought to my attention just recently, Mr. President, and I was unaware of this, but apparently Comcast offers a number of different services in addition to cable.

1003
01:27:48,329 --> 01:27:51,471
They offer security and fire alarm systems also.

1004
01:27:52,212 --> 01:27:53,693
And it was brought to my attention

1005
01:27:54,460 --> 01:28:04,865
as they refer to the life safety systems, that Massachusetts has a lot of rules and regulations that govern the life safety systems.

1006
01:28:05,585 --> 01:28:06,526
And the rules are clear.

1007
01:28:06,546 --> 01:28:11,888
In Massachusetts, all life safety system companies and their technicians must be licensed.

1008
01:28:12,548 --> 01:28:17,771
Every system they install must be inspected for code compliance by local authorities.

1009
01:28:18,391 --> 01:28:20,952
Earning a license takes years of education and training.

1010
01:28:21,420 --> 01:28:27,602
Maintaining a license requires continuing education to keep up with the latest technologies and building codes.

1011
01:28:28,063 --> 01:28:40,327
Furthermore, every employee of the security system company in Massachusetts has to pass a CORI criminal background check and obtain a state public safety certification of clearance every two years.

1012
01:28:40,908 --> 01:28:43,929
Comcast has disregarded these laws, Mr. President.

1013
01:28:45,029 --> 01:28:49,691
Apparently, there is a legal battle going on right now, but needless to say,

1014
01:28:50,293 --> 01:28:58,876
This should be a question that should be asked by whoever's signing the contract, and in our case, it's the mayor, on behalf of the residents.

1015
01:28:58,936 --> 01:29:11,341
If I'm a resident and I'm just looking through trying to get someone to provide a security system or a fire alarm in my house, I just look through and possibly, because I'm already doing business with Comcast, I would select them.

1016
01:29:12,042 --> 01:29:14,983
I would not be aware that they don't cover

1017
01:29:15,403 --> 01:29:26,808
the proper licenses, that their employees aren't checked with the CORI, criminal background check, and a host of other issues that are brought up, Mr. President.

1018
01:29:27,288 --> 01:29:44,395
And I think it's only appropriate that that be one of the questions, the connectivity issue and the question regarding their life safety systems, why they don't comply to state statute, which requires their workers to be CORI checked

1019
01:29:44,802 --> 01:29:48,384
and also to maintain compliance with local authorities.

1020
01:29:49,024 --> 01:29:53,506
And I would ask that that be part of the hearing on Thursday.

1021
01:29:54,046 --> 01:29:56,467
I, like other members of the council, I'm not sure if I can get there.

1022
01:29:56,547 --> 01:29:57,267
I work in town.

1023
01:29:57,728 --> 01:30:02,130
Two o'clock in the afternoon, that's why we asked to change it to six.

1024
01:30:02,570 --> 01:30:03,230
It's difficult.

1025
01:30:03,570 --> 01:30:04,971
And this is a very important issue.

1026
01:30:05,391 --> 01:30:09,773
This impacts everyone in the community, whether you have Comcast or Verizon.

1027
01:30:10,273 --> 01:30:13,835
Every person in the community is paying these high rates, Mr. President.

1028
01:30:14,798 --> 01:30:19,499
And as was mentioned by, I think it was Councilor Penta, the service you receive is lackluster.

1029
01:30:20,260 --> 01:30:24,881
And honestly, you know, they corner the market in this system.

1030
01:30:25,641 --> 01:30:31,182
You can get a disc on your house, one of those dishes, if you don't mind your house looking like a satellite.

1031
01:30:32,543 --> 01:30:41,145
I offered an ordinance back, I think it's got to be four years now, to regulate, maybe five years, to regulate the disc on the homes.

1032
01:30:41,665 --> 01:30:44,246
And to regulate the disc don't go on the front of the homes.

1033
01:30:45,784 --> 01:30:50,307
And when discs are no longer used, like my neighbor across the street has three of them on the front of the home.

1034
01:30:50,667 --> 01:30:51,648
It's a rental property.

1035
01:30:52,068 --> 01:30:53,870
They no longer, they have Comcast now.

