1297
01:50:44,191 --> 01:50:53,373
Offered by Councillor Marks, be it resolved that the Medford Traffic Commission review the resident permit parking enforcement hours on Placetid Road from Irving Street to Century Street.

1298
01:50:53,814 --> 01:50:56,675
Area residents pay for a residential permit sticker.

1299
01:50:57,055 --> 01:50:58,235
However, enforcement

1300
01:50:58,727 --> 01:51:01,168
only takes place between 11 p.m.

1301
01:51:01,248 --> 01:51:02,188
and 7 a.m.

1302
01:51:02,549 --> 01:51:03,309
Councillor Marks.

1303
01:51:03,969 --> 01:51:04,950
Thank you, Mr. President.

1304
01:51:05,030 --> 01:51:28,179
I was contacted by a resident on Playstead Road, and this has actually been an issue for a number of years, but most recently, because of the new parking enforcement and the resident permit parking, residents now are getting tickets in front of their home, which they pay for, a permit sticker, but the permit sticker doesn't go into effect

1305
01:51:29,221 --> 01:51:31,922
until after 11 p.m.

1306
01:51:32,882 --> 01:51:38,784
And the issue, Mr. President, is apparently along Playstead Road, we all know Playstead Park is there.

1307
01:51:39,244 --> 01:51:41,365
On the park side, you can park there.

1308
01:51:41,445 --> 01:51:42,745
It's not resident permit parking.

1309
01:51:42,765 --> 01:51:44,005
You can park there with no problem.

1310
01:51:44,765 --> 01:51:53,808
On the opposite side where the homes are, there's permit parking, but from, I believe it's Irving Street all the way up to Century Street,

1311
01:51:54,976 --> 01:52:06,321
The parking, it may not be the full length, but I know directly across from Playstead Park, the enforcement is after the hours of 11 p.m.

1312
01:52:07,201 --> 01:52:11,883
until 7 a.m., so you can't park there unless you have a permit sticker between those hours.

1313
01:52:12,244 --> 01:52:19,647
But residents that may get home at six o'clock, seven o'clock, eight o'clock, coming home to an area, they can't find a parking spot.

1314
01:52:20,307 --> 01:52:22,748
And I think the whole intent with permit parking

1315
01:52:23,172 --> 01:52:28,454
is to at least give residents the opportunity to park near their home or on their street.

1316
01:52:29,035 --> 01:52:49,164
So I would ask that the Traffic Commission review this policy to see if there's anything we can do to make it so residents that are paying for a permit parking sticker receive the same benefits that everyone else receives, that if it's a permit parking street, only people with permits can park there.

1317
01:52:49,564 --> 01:52:50,965
And currently, that's not the case

1318
01:52:51,458 --> 01:52:53,199
on a good portion of Playstead Road.

1319
01:52:53,579 --> 01:52:55,379
So I'd ask that that be reviewed, Mr. President.

1320
01:52:56,520 --> 01:52:58,140
Thank you, Councilor Mox.

1321
01:52:58,180 --> 01:52:59,061
Councilor Caravaglia.

1322
01:52:59,081 --> 01:52:59,961
Thank you, Mr. President.

1323
01:52:59,981 --> 01:53:01,862
I echo Councilor Mox's sentiments.

1324
01:53:02,722 --> 01:53:03,982
I've seen the people of West Medford.

1325
01:53:04,002 --> 01:53:13,626
I've heard the complaints about the cars parking there, especially now with the kiosks being there and the commuters are starting to slide off onto all those other streets now.

1326
01:53:14,526 --> 01:53:16,487
And actually, it isn't just on those streets.

1327
01:53:17,147 --> 01:53:20,468
It's pretty much all on that all high street Playstead Road bus line.

1328
01:53:21,784 --> 01:53:25,886
they're all getting a little, all those streets are getting a little clogged up with the commuters.

1329
01:53:26,646 --> 01:53:29,287
So again, I support Councilor Marks' petition.

1330
01:53:29,327 --> 01:53:34,729
Thank you, Councilor Kerrio.

1331
01:53:34,769 --> 01:53:36,209
Thank you, Councilor Marks, for bringing this up.

1332
01:53:36,709 --> 01:53:48,153
I brought this up a few weeks ago on two separate occasions relative to cars being swinged over there, but it's a result of the 16 cars that were allowed to park

1333
01:53:48,748 --> 01:53:51,109
on the corner of Winthrop Street and Playstead Road.

1334
01:53:52,230 --> 01:53:54,911
And right now, you're lucky if there's one car there a day.

1335
01:53:55,151 --> 01:53:59,914
So take the average of 15 cars a day not being there at $5 a day.

1336
01:53:59,934 --> 01:54:01,235
That's $75 a day.

1337
01:54:01,735 --> 01:54:08,679
Once a month is $300, times 12 is $3,600 a year that they're not getting that they anticipated.

1338
01:54:09,199 --> 01:54:13,381
And by pushing these cars onto the side streets over there, you're just going to compound.

1339
01:54:13,401 --> 01:54:14,782
You're going to create another problem.

1340
01:54:15,199 --> 01:54:18,880
that the resident parking, that these cars that are not capable of doing.

1341
01:54:19,960 --> 01:54:30,922
I have a letter, which I'll bring next week, from a resident who tells me on four particular occasions how she had to go out and help people, not only negotiate the meter, but the glare.

1342
01:54:31,322 --> 01:54:34,742
Going right back to what you said, Rick, the glare of the meter, you can't see it.

1343
01:54:35,142 --> 01:54:37,323
It's unreadable.

1344
01:54:38,263 --> 01:54:41,203
Who put money in the meter did not get the right receipt that came back.

1345
01:54:41,563 --> 01:54:43,224
One got a receipt, two people later,

1346
01:54:45,142 --> 01:54:47,824
Another one put the money in the meter, got four quarters back for his quarter.

1347
01:54:48,564 --> 01:54:49,505
It's a stupid system.

1348
01:54:50,245 --> 01:54:52,887
And it's the stupidest thing that this mayor could have ever come up with.

1349
01:54:54,188 --> 01:54:58,311
He could resolve his whole legacy if he just comes forward and says, listen, we made a mistake.

1350
01:54:58,331 --> 01:54:59,151
We're going to get rid of it.

1351
01:54:59,411 --> 01:55:05,636
And we're going to go revert ourselves back to a local, as Councilor Marks alluded to, a revenue traffic enforcement program.

1352
01:55:05,676 --> 01:55:06,536
And we'll do it in-house.

1353
01:55:06,896 --> 01:55:07,877
And we'll start slow.

1354
01:55:07,997 --> 01:55:08,858
And we'll move forward.

1355
01:55:09,358 --> 01:55:11,099
This thing is not helping anybody.

1356
01:55:11,359 --> 01:55:12,520
You can go to the business.

1357
01:55:12,560 --> 01:55:13,821
The business merchants will tell you.

1358
01:55:14,285 --> 01:55:15,485
It is not helping us.

1359
01:55:15,666 --> 01:55:16,966
As a matter of fact, it's so unfair.

1360
01:55:17,386 --> 01:55:22,968
You go to West Medford, they still have a meter in front of a residential home, but people are still trying to put it in, and they're not supposed to.

1361
01:55:23,268 --> 01:55:26,250
That meter should have been taken out of there months ago, and it's still there.

1362
01:55:26,710 --> 01:55:34,533
How do you put a meter in front of a dentist, a one-dentist-person office on High Street, and the other one in front of a — in front of a what?

1363
01:55:35,533 --> 01:55:36,934
We'd call it a funeral home, okay?

1364
01:55:37,034 --> 01:55:38,034
I mean, it's unfair.

1365
01:55:38,054 --> 01:55:39,795
It's just — it just doesn't make any sense at all.

1366
01:55:40,695 --> 01:55:41,775
It's a killer to the city.

1367
01:55:41,875 --> 01:55:43,116
It's anti-business.

1368
01:55:43,647 --> 01:55:44,867
It's anti-citizen.

1369
01:55:44,887 --> 01:55:46,708
It's just anti-everything.

1370
01:55:47,548 --> 01:55:49,289
Medford is not downtown Boston.

1371
01:55:49,309 --> 01:55:50,689
It is not these places.

1372
01:55:51,449 --> 01:55:58,591
And as Councilor Mark's resolution points out, it's forcing people to go to other parts of the community to park their cars.

1373
01:55:58,931 --> 01:56:03,873
And you're going to start to see people really getting pedoed with people parking in front of their houses.

1374
01:56:03,893 --> 01:56:08,894
And you're going to see some damage done to these cars, because people, you know, someone turned around and sold something.

1375
01:56:08,914 --> 01:56:09,934
You can't tell me where to park.

1376
01:56:09,994 --> 01:56:11,635
I can go to the public street, and I can park here.

1377
01:56:11,675 --> 01:56:12,735
And this is the issue.

1378
01:56:13,627 --> 01:56:20,092
So this issue was really compounded and multiplied itself and it needs to be resolved immediately before something happens.

1379
01:56:20,532 --> 01:56:24,215
Something personal happens to the property and something personal happens to someone.

1380
01:56:24,515 --> 01:56:26,957
If physical altercations take place because of this.

1381
01:56:27,297 --> 01:56:28,638
So I thank you for putting that forward.

1382
01:56:28,678 --> 01:56:36,264
And I would ask Mr. President, Councilor Marks, I would ask that you forward, you want a response from the chief of police on this immediately, immediately on this matter.

1383
01:56:36,744 --> 01:56:40,987
So the motion of Councilor Marks as amended by Councilor Penta, Madam Citizen.

1384
01:56:41,778 --> 01:56:44,439
Hi, Jean Martington coming straight, and I'm glad you brought this up, Mr. Marks.

1385
01:56:44,559 --> 01:56:50,761
I was just talking to a senior citizen today who often goes down, she lives in Medford, and she goes down to the senior center and all that.

1386
01:56:51,581 --> 01:57:06,466
She said that there's a lot of abuse of those placards, that people will take somebody's, you know, one of their relatives' placards, and put it on their car, and then is able to park in one of those, you know,

1387
01:57:07,374 --> 01:57:08,735
spots, the handicapped spots.

1388
01:57:09,196 --> 01:57:10,236
So I just wanted to bring that up.

1389
01:57:10,277 --> 01:57:23,747
So whoever is monitoring, whether it's the private company or whether it's the police, to just, she says that people cover the faces of the person and that they need to show the face of the person and try to clean that up because it's not right.

1390
01:57:24,107 --> 01:57:29,271
The people that need those spots should have those spots and the people that don't should walk.

1391
01:57:29,591 --> 01:57:29,832
Thank you.

1392
01:57:39,710 --> 01:57:41,250
just briefly, Mr. President.

1393
01:57:42,391 --> 01:57:51,472
I think we're at the point, and we all took a vote recently, but I think we're at the point right now, Mr. President, that we really need to revisit this parking program.

1394
01:57:52,232 --> 01:58:08,295
And we had a meeting a couple of weeks ago, and we got a listing of the revenue that's coming in for the program, but we still haven't addressed the needs of the business community and the residents that I've been talking to, Mr. President, regarding these kiosks.

1395
01:58:08,901 --> 01:58:15,983
I think people are all in favor of moving cars along and providing consistent enforcement throughout the community.

1396
01:58:16,443 --> 01:58:20,045
I haven't heard one person say, you know what, we don't want enforcement.

1397
01:58:20,465 --> 01:58:27,287
People want enforcement, business owners want enforcement, the pay for parking program needs to be revisited in this community.

1398
01:58:27,647 --> 01:58:36,470
Now whether it's this mayor or the next mayor, that is the subject that I'm hearing out there in the community, and I'm not sure why the mayor's not willing to have a conversation

1399
01:58:36,964 --> 01:58:39,786
Maybe he's just going to let it be on the plate of the next person.

1400
01:58:40,246 --> 01:58:46,791
But it's definitely the topic that's out there now, and the dialogue needs to take place sooner than later, Mr. President.

